<title>UK: Murdoch to &quot;mortgage&quot; BSkyB stake - report.</title>
<headline>Murdoch to &quot;mortgage&quot; BSkyB stake - report.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Rupert Murdoch plans to mortgage part of his stake in satellite broadcaster BSkyB in order to raise up to $2 billion to finance development elsewhere in his media empire, the Independent reported on Thursday.</p>
<p>News America Holdings, a U.S.-based subsidiary of Murdoch's News Corp, is seeking to raise the money through an issue of preference shares, convertible at a pre-determined price into BSkyB shares, the report added.</p>
